description: My parents took video of this coyote when they went for a hike at Mission Peak

Seriously Matt, how do you do it? I was pretty psyched to see this fellow, but he definitely did not feel the same, and trotted off post haste. I guess something more than a 18-55mm would have helped...

Why won't they stay still.  And come closer.  Interestingly, as they were passing, I heard this big chorus of squeaks, but I couldn't quite spot the squeakers.  Could it have been the ground squirrels giving alert calls from their burrows?  Do they do that?
